-- Borg Sees Little Alternative to Greek Euro Exit: Radio Sweden
-- B y   J o s i a n e   K r e m e r
-- 2012-10-13T09:16:03Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-13/borg-sees-little-alternative-to-greek-euro-exit-radio-sweden.html
It’s hard to see an alternative to
Greece abandoning the euro, even though this process would be
painful and difficult, Swedish Finance Minister  Anders Borg  told
Sveriges Radio.  Greece might become more competitive and get back on its
feet after quitting the single-currency bloc, Borg said in an
 article  published late yesterday on the Swedish broadcaster’s
website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Josiane Kremer in Oslo at 
